<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF53FF931D95FECE9A56FD1B" pageId="14" pageNumber="265" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF53FF931D95FECE99F2FDA3" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF53FF931D95FECE99F8FEFA" bold="true" box="[199,462,330,356]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Based on the presence of six dorsal striae and a submarginal stria on each elytron, the new species can be classified within 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF53FF931F13FEEB9ACBFE16" authorityName="Regimbart" authorityYear="1899" box="[577,765,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irinus">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF53FF931F13FEEB9ACBFE16" box="[577,765,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">Copelatus irinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. Elongate habitus, complete elytral striation and male median lobe without distinct process place 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF53FF931FBCFE179BABFE33" authority="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek, 2022" authorityName="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek" authorityYear="2022" box="[750,925,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanlingensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF53FF931FBCFE179BABFE33" box="[750,925,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">C. nanlingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="88F27A30BF53FF931EF7FE179BCAFE33" box="[933,1020,403,429]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF53FF931919FE179CEFFE32" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1884" box="[1099,1241,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF53FF931919FE179CEFFE32" box="[1099,1241,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">C. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex. Within the complex, the new species can be recognised based on smaller size and very broad basal orange band on elytra; however, the indubitable identification of 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF53FF931F2CFE5F9B06FE6B" authority="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek, 2022" authorityName="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek" authorityYear="2022" box="[638,816,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanlingensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF53FF931F2CFE5F9B06FE6B" box="[638,816,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">C. nanlingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="88F27A30BF53FF931E68FE5F9BA2FE6B" box="[826,916,475,501]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is only possible based on the shape of male genitalia: straight median lobe with hook-like apical part is very characteristic for the new species, and unique among Chinese 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF53FF931C1EFDA79988FDA3" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1832" box="[332,446,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF53FF931C1EFDA79988FDA3" box="[332,446,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">Copelatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF53FF931D95FDC29A56FD1B" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF53FF931D95FDC29996FDFE" bold="true" box="[199,416,582,608]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">Collection details.</emphasis>
All 
<typeStatus id="7E0EA5FBBF53FF931C85FDC39A31FDFF" box="[471,519,583,609]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected at the border of shallow pool with sand bottom and numerous decaying tree leaves (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF53FF931CADFDEF9A65FD1B" box="[511,595,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–78" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,181,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-23@42.[180,1408,181,1848]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 71–78. Habitat of Copelatus in China. 71. Tianmushan, Zhejiang (C. chinensis); 72. Jinggangshan, Jiangxi (C. dentatipenis sp. nov.); 73. Tongbiguan, Yunnan (C. diversistriatus sp. nov.). 74. Dadongshan, Guangdong (C. nanlingensis sp. nov.); 75. Macao (C. oblitus in wet soil); 76. Dali, Yunnan (C. rimosus); 77. Kongshu, Yunnan (C. rosulae sp. nov.); 78. Danxiashan, Guangdong (C. oblitus and C. zimmermanni)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411118/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF53FF931D95FD0B9A5CFD53" pageId="14" pageNumber="265" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF53FF931D95FD0B9A5CFD53" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF53FF931D95FD0B9978FD37" bold="true" box="[199,334,655,681]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after the Nanling mountain range where it was collected. The specific epithet is an adjective in the nominative singular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF53FF931D95FD529A77FC8B" pageId="14" pageNumber="265" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF53FF931D95FD529A77FC8B" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF53FF931D95FD529957FD6E" bold="true" box="[199,353,726,752]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">Distribution.</emphasis>
So far known only from the 
<typeStatus id="7E0EA5FBBF53FF931FE1FD539AD5FD6F" box="[691,739,727,753]" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">type</typeStatus>
locality in Dadongshan mountains, Nanling mountain range, northern 
<collectingRegion id="6371D5BBBF53FF931DAFFD7F99B5FC8B" box="[253,387,763,789]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D9A25BC9BF53FF931CDCFD7F99E7FC8B" box="[398,465,763,789]" name="China" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">China</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF53FF931CB2FD7F9A02FC8B" box="[480,564,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 82" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1078,1102]" captionTargetBox="[265,1326,188,1049]" captionTargetId="figure-23@44.[258,1330,181,1054]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 82. Map of distribution of Copelatus in China Mainland." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410810" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410810/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="265">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
